to the editor re stroke centers try to speed response time news article july 27 the new york state department of health 's program to reduce hospital response time for treating victims of stroke is an important but incomplete first step for more effective treatment also critically important is educating the public especially those in high risk groups of the warning signs of a stroke and the urgent need to call 911 for help transportation to the hospital diagnosis and treatment with thrombolytic drugs must all occur within three hours of the attack to reduce the severity of stroke jeffrey perls wilton conn july 27 2003 the writer is a physician assistant

